comments: Nurkic (POR) and Giddey (OKC) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Grant (POR) releases away and incidental contact occurs with Dort (OKC) as Dort goes under the pick.
Nurkic (POR) and Muscala (OKC) briefly come together off-ball and marginal contact occurs.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings his arm toward Lillard's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Muscala (OKC) jumps alongside Lillard's (POR) path and maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt.
Grant (POR) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Simons (POR) brings his arm toward Dort's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Dort's drive.
Lillard (POR) and Giddey (OKC) mutually engage in pursuit of the rebound.
Lillard (POR) and Giddey (OKC) both make simultaneous contact with the ball, and a jump ball is correctly assessed.
Nurkic (POR) and Dort (OKC) briefly come together as they both move up the court, and the contact is marginal.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Lillard's (POR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Muscala (OKC) and Nurkic (POR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.

Nurkic's (POR) hand grazes Williams (OKC) as Giddey retrieves and secures the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Hart (POR) commits a take foul on Giddey (OKC).
Johnson (POR) commits a take foul on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
